# Basics-of-Programming-Java-Programming

Multiplication
easy
Problem Statement
Given two numbers m and n, multiply them using only "addition" operations.
Input
User Task:
Since this will be a functional problem, you don't have to take input. You just have to complete the function Multiply() that takes the integer M and N as a parameter.

Constraints:
1 ≤ T ≤ 100
0 ≤ M, N ≤ 100
Output
Return the product of N and M.
Example
Sample Input
2
2 3
3 4

Sample Output
6
12


///////////////**************////////////////



static int  Multiply_by_recursion(int N, int M) 
    { 
  //Enter your code here
  if(N==0 || M==0)
  {
    return 0;
  }
  if (M == 1)
  {
    return N;
  }
  return N + Multiply_by_recursion(N,M-1);
    }
